<subSubSection id="488C8AF2ABBE9115AA142519567EE4D5" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8876A098AF399B28C9CAE249144C491A" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ACCB6017A6E43A9E101389E0E5F7822B" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
The species epithet &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="A20CF61A6743D6FEFAF878C0C9E67D74" authorityName="Gupta &amp; van Achterberg" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Pambolus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pambolus infuscatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infuscatus">
<emphasis id="3E1B1544ADC69C94A7FD1BB9F3C5B065" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Pambolus infuscatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; is derived from the character of the wing which is largely infuscated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="53A939B0F2C3AC5D00863C946EF87DE0" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="BE0594194E9E78B0E019D16B9B0FF1D8" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6886BCDD64E69631C7B8D1DEAB5E7D95" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
Antenna of ♀ 1.3
<normalizedToken id="0DB528617D93FDA380FF124E57FF0CC0" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than body, without ivory or white apical segments and in total with about 24 segments; eye about 1.6 times longer than temple in dorsal view and temple gradually narrowed behind eyes (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F812D337314A8736EE6B1476D0BE3FA8" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Female holotype of Pambolus (Phaenodus) infuscatus Gupta &amp; van Achterberg sp. nov. A habitus B head (in frontal aspect) C vertex D mesosoma and metasoma (in dorsal aspect) E mesoscutum and scutellum (in dorsal aspect) F fore wing and hind wing G mesopleuron and propodeum (in lateral aspect)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81886.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677654" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">1C</figureCitation>
); propodeal spine distinctly protruding, longer than wide basally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4556F7CD6D8C7C1F37DC8FAA43D0E850" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Female holotype of Pambolus (Phaenodus) infuscatus Gupta &amp; van Achterberg sp. nov. A habitus B head (in frontal aspect) C vertex D mesosoma and metasoma (in dorsal aspect) E mesoscutum and scutellum (in dorsal aspect) F fore wing and hind wing G mesopleuron and propodeum (in lateral aspect)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81886.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677654" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">1A, G</figureCitation>
); vein 1-SR+M of fore wing distinctly bent; vein SR1 of fore wing 2.2
<normalizedToken id="C06FD5AFB831ECC5581ACA96600D17FC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than vein 3-SR; pterostigma 4.1
<normalizedToken id="61F396DC93EF3DE77E0158D6703D7B87" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2FACF839B05516429A83B23F8FB49E8D" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Female holotype of Pambolus (Phaenodus) infuscatus Gupta &amp; van Achterberg sp. nov. A fore wing B propodeum and T 1 C metasoma with hind femur and tibia." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81886.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677655" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">2A</figureCitation>
); hind femur about 3.8
<normalizedToken id="B04A708AAE2DB689B6A6C5A472488D91" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide; length of first tergite about equal to its apical width (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6F2F5D492C418D75CC19A6924CDC8AD6" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Female holotype of Pambolus (Phaenodus) infuscatus Gupta &amp; van Achterberg sp. nov. A fore wing B propodeum and T 1 C metasoma with hind femur and tibia." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81886.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677655" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">2B</figureCitation>
); second tergite smooth; setose part of ovipositor sheath 0.3
<normalizedToken id="5DEBC270FC70EB3CE4CE22EA25B8D6CF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as hind tibia (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B43913331586C998F396A2BEF8A3147F" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Female holotype of Pambolus (Phaenodus) infuscatus Gupta &amp; van Achterberg sp. nov. A fore wing B propodeum and T 1 C metasoma with hind femur and tibia." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81886.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677655" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">2C</figureCitation>
); pterostigma largely dark brown; fore wing membrane (except apex of wing) largely dark brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="36B2C252431512B5F85FFAC3C88DC3F2" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Female holotype of Pambolus (Phaenodus) infuscatus Gupta &amp; van Achterberg sp. nov. A fore wing B propodeum and T 1 C metasoma with hind femur and tibia." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81886.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677655" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">2A</figureCitation>
); hind femur and tibia largely dark brown, hind tarsus ivory.
</paragraph>
<caption id="3DE75FF85147CC0D476AC54C23EADBF5" doi="10.3897/jhr.90.81886.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677654" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" start="Figure 1" startId="F1">
<paragraph id="F3E97633B61CF39FA66A6516924B0949" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="EB6F585E2F2958AC815EDBC0B1CE4571" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Figure 1.</emphasis>
Female holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="6C1B44F0B59B28A8430A6C6452596E41" authorityName="Gupta &amp; van Achterberg" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Pambolus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pambolus (Phaenodus) infuscatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infuscatus" subGenus="Phaenodus">Pambolus (Phaenodus) infuscatus</taxonomicName>
Gupta &amp; van Achterberg sp. nov. 
<emphasis id="7676EB1E04A755036440C53DD36AAE75" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">A</emphasis>
habitus 
<emphasis id="B2F253EB6524DC02848D44C8680AC6F0" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">B</emphasis>
head (in frontal aspect) 
<emphasis id="86AA73D3BE4C3F81872564FF19A6298E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">C</emphasis>
vertex 
<emphasis id="9B2553186472F7DC33581F9CD6CDE9A3" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">D</emphasis>
mesosoma and metasoma (in dorsal aspect) 
<emphasis id="1FD793E3760CAF30B9A6BE8D32275AF8" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">E</emphasis>
mesoscutum and scutellum (in dorsal aspect) 
<emphasis id="6392EF8E160B6CCF188144E6672C42B1" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">F</emphasis>
fore wing and hind wing 
<emphasis id="4E50B13EDC73CEEA9A876756A727737A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">G</emphasis>
mesopleuron and propodeum (in lateral aspect).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="993EF29D07ED65D2C8EA4D94D94443E2" doi="10.3897/jhr.90.81886.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677655" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
<paragraph id="0D7E191927C3B7E271602A1A3F13F600" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="5552AFE911D26428CE82EDE3D7F7E89A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Figure 2.</emphasis>
Female holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="F49F0AFE88992870106F1D3F8823111F" authorityName="Gupta &amp; van Achterberg" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Pambolus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pambolus (Phaenodus) infuscatus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infuscatus" subGenus="Phaenodus">Pambolus (Phaenodus) infuscatus</taxonomicName>
Gupta &amp; van Achterberg sp. nov. 
<emphasis id="FBCC09E37FCCAF56199D78CB33B8F6AD" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">A</emphasis>
fore wing 
<emphasis id="BB56D6BDF9AAD1BFCEB5D4692E1A0E5E" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">B</emphasis>
propodeum and T1 
<emphasis id="9BC2C4EFEA3C533AB40CED2530DA4D8B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">C</emphasis>
metasoma with hind femur and tibia.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F4ED9E181DADC9D476FEFBBDE9CCF558" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="description">
<paragraph id="239179F05FCACF14924F8B6FCF0B7216" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F1FD10455581A927C7894DD43BDFC214" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B29EA21E50890F0A9EF968D57B82F32A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Female.</emphasis>
Body length 3.0 mm; fore wing length 2.5 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="920552C0E72ED676DD1C9A28E9EA5977" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="EA5D58A598879BB82490CEEF74E83702" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Head.</emphasis>
Antenna 24 segmented, 1.3
<normalizedToken id="A77A4A78522CEED7397DE6094E3433D8" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as body; scape 1.5
<normalizedToken id="18ACFA59CEA7A53A22F11A8272223E01" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide, F1 3.2
<normalizedToken id="9748D0A010263ACB4F5364D959213463" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide and as long as F2; head transverse, ca. 1.1
<normalizedToken id="F7743D80AFEB8AEDC75D589143E43B13" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as long in dorsal view, temple smooth, distinctly widening ventrally, widest distance from eyes 2.0
<normalizedToken id="D0BE9AF1B8D3711F9D93577EA962CBBD" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as eye dorsally; eye length 1.6
<normalizedToken id="0795E6E180791996EEDD0BBF1F73A020" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
temple in dorsal view (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D763850906131219C688825AF23296E2" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Female holotype of Pambolus (Phaenodus) infuscatus Gupta &amp; van Achterberg sp. nov. A habitus B head (in frontal aspect) C vertex D mesosoma and metasoma (in dorsal aspect) E mesoscutum and scutellum (in dorsal aspect) F fore wing and hind wing G mesopleuron and propodeum (in lateral aspect)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81886.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677654" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">1C</figureCitation>
); POL: OOL: OD = 7: 13: 5; malar space 3.8
<normalizedToken id="832A3D8B8943676AF98E9119F7393428" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
basal width of mandible; face transversely rugulose and setose, clypeus smooth, distinctly separated from face, vertex finely granulate around ocelli with shallow rugae, vertex and occiput rather transversely rugulo-rugose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D99B34DF4DED497821B16CE0ED9924C3" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="8F88B04846AFA73FFB8B2B4CF664EFCE" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Mesosoma.</emphasis>
Mesosoma 1.7
<normalizedToken id="D3D88931D9BD6FB6E03D8D9E000A3A93" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide in dorsal view, median and lateral lobes of mesoscutum granulate-reticulate, sparsely setose; notauli indistinct anteriorly surrounded by strong crenulae, rather prominent posteriorly; scutellar sulcus deep and broad with six crenulae, mesoscutum median length 2
<normalizedToken id="22A57BD58418DA3C45E6CCC5D59F0473" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as scutellum, propodeal spine triangular-shaped (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CDFF99A42BA154EAE2014517D2301557" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Female holotype of Pambolus (Phaenodus) infuscatus Gupta &amp; van Achterberg sp. nov. A habitus B head (in frontal aspect) C vertex D mesosoma and metasoma (in dorsal aspect) E mesoscutum and scutellum (in dorsal aspect) F fore wing and hind wing G mesopleuron and propodeum (in lateral aspect)." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81886.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677654" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">1A</figureCitation>
), shorter than second and third tarsomeres of hind tarsus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="58708ABB64DEEA9C6C57D311CE0A5836" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="1681E02F77288BEA87DE39A69480D382" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Wings.</emphasis>
Fore wing 3.1
<normalizedToken id="9E662EAAEEC1B17251416B5518C7E8E8" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide, 2.4
<normalizedToken id="BFA0B24BCD62CD09CD4945E2F3F02FE7" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as hind tibia; pterostigma 4.1
<normalizedToken id="283872139FBA8B4C0D5926B4572ADFFC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide, 0.7
<normalizedToken id="98748BFCFA23FEEFF36423456986143F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
length of R1, r arising slightly behind middle of pterostigma; r almost subequal width of pterostigma; 3-SR 1.6
<normalizedToken id="6F0525FBD1BB102CF71CB4CAC7FC2CFB" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as r, 1.2
<normalizedToken id="6DF358BE8475514255225A624C2A42C0" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-SR, 0.5
<normalizedToken id="0ABD7F295B926FBB9D87FEE53F9AC0D8" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
SR1; r-m 0.6
<normalizedToken id="6401991AD5523CFEB130EF6C1270F15B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-SR; marginal cell 2.5
<normalizedToken id="137CF73918C0421FDDFFEB0BE69C925C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as wide as high, SR1 bent at an angle; 1-SR+M bent (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="287155FBA3578957FEAC8DE8EAE06CB6" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Female holotype of Pambolus (Phaenodus) infuscatus Gupta &amp; van Achterberg sp. nov. A fore wing B propodeum and T 1 C metasoma with hind femur and tibia." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81886.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677655" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">2A</figureCitation>
); hind wing 5.5
<normalizedToken id="773194E59504B3FB31BAB76182F740E7" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="27693E67C3B8517875812846B7FD8637" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="CB07D20C5392AB9ED4E9442F32CCC0CE" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Legs.</emphasis>
Hind leg setose, hind femur 3.8
<normalizedToken id="B90E5C7AF39965F84C18B0E48BECA3CC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide, hind tarsus almost as long as hind tibia, hind basitarsus 0.7
<normalizedToken id="D061119133390B06F0790116318CC570" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as tarsal segment 2-4 combined.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B8095F661B26465CD9AD98BBCE58A30" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="0488E8D43638D08FFC8C360D4D1E155A" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Metasoma.</emphasis>
Metasoma 0.7
<normalizedToken id="F4EAC3EFF78AADC158208018DD38F920" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as head and mesosoma combined in lateral view; T1 longitudinally striated, strongly broadening posteriorly; T1 0.9
<normalizedToken id="7F627D33D7B4C9C0CE00CA2ACB32FD9A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad apically, spiracles almost near middle; remaining tergites smooth; ovipositor sheath 0.8
<normalizedToken id="FFBF5296BC81D97D6D6DBD26E6CCCBD0" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as tarsomere 2-4 combined; setose part of ovipositor sheath 0.3
<normalizedToken id="659C23392CAB7D5BF54864F8B209A613" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as hind tibia; ovipositor short, straight and pointed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="32A04E740D243EFEFBF2EDEBDF9ADEEE" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="546664296791DD26427B900DD2415C73" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Colour.</emphasis>
Head yellowish brown with dark brown patches; eyes grey, stemmaticum, propleuron, mesopleuron, propodeum black on edges; mesonotum dark brown except yellowish notaulic region (middle and posterior), legs in general brownish except pale trochantellus, yellowish tarsi and dark brown hind femur and tibia (but bases of femur and tibia pale); metasoma reddish brown; T1 yellowish brown with darker edges, ovipositor sheath dark brown; mandibles yellowish brown; tip of mandibles and tarsal claws dark brown, antennal segment F1-F10 yellowish brown; F11-F22 dark brown; ocelli transparent; wings infuscate except apical one fourth, pterostigma dark brown, veins brown, but veins SR1 (except base) and apical half of vein 1-R1 yellow and veins r and r-m subhyaline (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F54E10E9B06FF8F8DB72164DA9BEBE0C" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Female holotype of Pambolus (Phaenodus) infuscatus Gupta &amp; van Achterberg sp. nov. A fore wing B propodeum and T 1 C metasoma with hind femur and tibia." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.90.81886.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/677655" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">2A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4138C83C393238536E0F29BA0465CAB2" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="AF8AEF9CE531E08A03734D2FCF7BAB26" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Male.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D762CD2DA3C01DB4FFAFBC9AFF986980" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="host">
<paragraph id="1FC7BAAA625F70B99F673CC1DBF80A69" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Host.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FEBEF7D47C2A2FCF77AB136E84CF3F03" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B02A2E910633FA4129E6A5D4BDBD3361" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B11E3C9261ABA15371B18392B36AFF07" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="709BC574DB3BA96CDAAB47F675CDB229" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">India (Himachal Pradesh).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="12EEA7C504F00FD05C948671EA9FD7B1" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="D913AE56E69A728FD44EEA6A0DF78929" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B9E5BEC116871182D08BCDCF711FDF2A" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">
This new species comes near to 
<taxonomicName id="FEF155134AEC60647141CD150A0E9DE5" authorityName="Papp" authorityYear="1996" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Pambolus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pambolus (Ph.) topali" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="topali" subGenus="Ph.">Pambolus (Ph.) topali</taxonomicName>
Papp, 1996, however differs in the following characters: Eyes about 1.6
<normalizedToken id="737712D6BC7799BA816E59A87BD08930" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as temple in dorsal view; hind femur 3.8 times longer than broad medially and antenna with 24 segments (
<emphasis id="D865C8692621EFB1C6DC92D3EAE6E8B6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="59">vs</emphasis>
eyes about 2.0
<normalizedToken id="59BC3FD8B3C3EB22A489B476AA231621" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as temple in dorsal view; hind femur 4.6-5.0
<normalizedToken id="42C84B25642298E7CC860D1267E76869" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as broad medially; antenna with 27-30 segments).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
